Now I can see the full picture clearly:

**Fix 1 (Line 88):** `variant={ButtonVariant.plain}` — The value `plain` is valid in both the old and new type union. The type change only *added* `'stateful'`. No code change needed.

**Fix 2 (Line 84-91):** The `<Button>` contains only `<MinusCircleIcon />` as a child (icon-only case). Per the migration rule, I need to move the icon to the `icon` prop and make the Button self-closing:

Before:
```jsx
<Button
  onClick={() => {
    onDelete(id);
  }}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
>
  <MinusCircleIcon />
</Button>
```

After:
```jsx
<Button
  onClick={() => {
    onDelete(id);
  }}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
  icon={<MinusCircleIcon />}
/>
```

After this change, `MinusCircleIcon` is still used (in the `icon` prop), so the import stays. Let me apply the edit:

